rhapsody in august ( &lt;&lt;unk&gt;&gt; &lt;&lt;unk&gt;&gt; no &lt;&lt;unk&gt;&gt; ( &lt;&lt;unk&gt;&gt; no &lt;&lt;unk&gt;&gt; ) ) is a 1991 japanese film by akira kurosawa . the story centers on an elderly hibakusha , who lost her husband in the 1945 atomic bombing of nagasaki , caring for her four grandchildren over the summer . she learns of a long-lost brother , &lt;&lt;unk&gt;&gt; , living in hawaii who wants her to visit him before he dies . american film star richard gere appears as &lt;&lt;unk&gt;&gt; 's son clark . the film was selected as the japanese entry for the best foreign language film at the 64th academy awards , but was not accepted as a nominee .